<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[140,1108,237,510]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">
Since the publication of 
<bibRefCitation author="Brandt A" box="[413,588,237,263]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" refId="ref22168" refString="Brandt A (1988) Antarctic Serolidae and Cirolanidae (Crustacea: Isopoda): New Genera, New Species, and Redescriptions. Koeltz Scientific Books, Koenigstein, Germany, 143 pp." type="book" year="1988">Brandt’s (1988)</bibRefCitation>
review there has been a proliferation of genera within the 
<taxonomicName box="[264,371,272,298]" class="Malacostraca" family="Serolidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Serolidae</taxonomicName>
. Prior to that date five genera were recognised; the publication of six new genera by 
<bibRefCitation author="Wagele J-W" box="[346,512,307,334]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" pagination="3 - 69" refId="ref23941" refString="Wagele J-W (1994) Notes on Antarctic and South American Serolidae (Crustacea, Isopoda) with remarks on the phylogenetic biogeography and a description of new genera. Zoologische Jahrbucher der Systematik 121: 3 - 69." type="journal article" year="1994">Wägele (1994)</bibRefCitation>
brought the total to 20 genera. Th e most recent key, to any region, is that of 
<bibRefCitation author="Brandt A" box="[422,589,343,369]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" refId="ref22168" refString="Brandt A (1988) Antarctic Serolidae and Cirolanidae (Crustacea: Isopoda): New Genera, New Species, and Redescriptions. Koeltz Scientific Books, Koenigstein, Germany, 143 pp." type="book" year="1988">Brandt (1988)</bibRefCitation>
, and that work no longer reflects the generic composition of the family. Th e key provided here is intended only to operate for the genera known to occur in the Indo-Pacific, the region bounded by East Africa in the west, eastwards to 
<collectingRegion box="[355,443,448,474]" country="United States of America" name="Hawaii" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">Hawai’i</collectingRegion>
and the island nations of Oceania (e.g. see 
<bibRefCitation author="Briggs JC" box="[952,1095,448,474]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" refId="ref22462" refString="Briggs JC (1974) Marine Zoogeography. McGraw-Hill, New York, xiv, 475 pp." type="book" year="1974">Briggs 1974</bibRefCitation>
). Th e key also serves to emphasize the character states now in use in defining genera.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
